text.section:
The Board may issue a temporary license to any applicant who:
Submits to a criminal history records check in accordance with § 8-303 of this subtitle;
Is licensed by any other state; or
Has taken and passed an examination under this title, but is waiting for the completion of the criminal history records check;
Submits to the Board:
An application on the form required by the Board;
Written, verified evidence that the requirement of item (1) of this subsection is being met; and
Any other document required by the Board; and
Pays the fee required by the Board.
